full_threads.body:
Hi Heath,

Are we able to add these two staff members, I'll have third but awaiting photos from Tim.

Ms Samira Gholamzadeh (BOHsc)
Oral Health Therapist

Samira is an experienced Oral Health Therapist and has a Bachelor of OHT from Charles Sturt University. She is a member of the DHAA and the Australian Dental and Oral Health Therapists Association.

As an Oral Health Therapist, Samira is thorough and has a unique preventive approach. She provides quality dental care to children and adults and always tries to cultivate informative consultations with constructive solutions in the treatment process.

As well as working at Annandale Dental, Samira works for a Periodontal and Implant Specialist Practice in Sydney. She is passionate about the field of periodontal management and provides not only general dental hygiene treatment but also periodontal therapy.

Samira believes educating people in the context of oral health and building mutual trust in the dental practice plays a pivotal role in helping patients. She says she feels motivated when her patients overcome anxiety or fear during and after treatment.

Outside of the clinic, Samira enjoys swimming, traveling, and spending time with family and friends.



Dr David Stuchmcke BSc, DDS, FRACS
Associate Dentist

"When a patient comes to see me, my goal is to make sure their concerns are listened to and that they feel that they are in a safe, comfortable environment. For a lot of people, coming to the dentist is a scary thing, and I want to try and alleviate that anxiety so that we can work out a plan that leaves the patient feeling like they are the very best version of themselves."

David Graduated with a Bachelor of Science from UQ in 2010 and studied dentistry at the University of Sydney graduating in 2015. He has experience in all aspects of general dentistry and is currently completing his Orthodontic speciality training at the University of Sydney .

David understands that for many people coming to the dentist can be an unpleasant experience, so he endeavours to make every patient visit as comfortable as possible.

David enjoys all aspects of dentistry and tries to take a preventative approach where possible. He strongly believes in educating his patients about the importance of home care maintenance. David believes that communication is imperative to the responsibilities of a dentist and always aims to clearly and adequately explain things to his patients in a manner that is easy to understand.

When David is not at work he enjoys cooking, reading, running and spending time at the beach.


Can we also just check the second photo of Mo as it is super zoomed in, I've also attached a different photo for Toni if we're able to swap that please.

Much appreciated

Dr Corbin Barry BDS (JCU)
Principal Dentist
